From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: StormLiangMS <stormliang@microsoft.com>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 17:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Enable FREE_MMAP_PROT_NONE for Linux

Without this define, MallocExtension_ReleaseToSystem() does not
actually release memory back to the OS on Linux. This is required
for the FRR tcmalloc memory release timer to function correctly.

Reference: FRR doc/developer/building-tcmalloc.rst

Signed-off-by: StormLiangMS <stormliang@microsoft.com>
---
 configure.ac | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -53,4 +53,5 @@ case "$host" in
    *-cygwin*) default_enable_heap_checker=no; default_enable_cpu_profiler=no;;
    *-freebsd*) default_enable_heap_checker=no;;
    *-darwin*) default_enable_heap_checker=no;;
+   *-linux*) AC_DEFINE(FREE_MMAP_PROT_NONE, 1, [Use mmap PROT_NONE to release memory on Linux]);;
 esac
